# SwimStats Chile — agent conventions

Before proposing changes, read:

- `conventions/AGENTS.en.md` (English operational rules)
- `conventions/ai_workflow.en.md` (session methodology)
- `AGENTS.md` (Spanish canonical rules)

## Non-negotiables

- Pipeline stages are decoupled: scrape → download → parse → curate → validate → load. Do not merge responsibilities.
- Never run `--load` unless the user explicitly requests a core load.
- One document in `requires_review` must not block or contaminate others in the same manifest.
- Athlete identity is not rigidly tied to club; use `core.athlete_current_club` and historical clubs as context.
- Minimal, localized patches. Explain diagnosis before editing.
- After Python/parser changes: run `pytest backend/tests`.
- Never commit passwords, `.env`, or raw/private data.

## Project agents

Specialized skills live in `.cursor/skills/`. Use them when asked; they do not replace these global rules.
